The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, gave a speech at Gerdau Steel in Saint Paul, Minnesota, highlighting the success of American steel and the strong economy. Pence praised President Trump's efforts in fighting for American workers and American-made steel. He mentioned that in the past two years, over 5.8 million new jobs have been created, with wages rising at the fastest pace in over a decade. Pence also emphasized the importance of passing the U.S.-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA), stating that it will level the playing field for American workers and create more opportunities. He urged the steelworkers to spread the word about the importance of passing the USMCA and to continue supporting the growth of American steel and manufacturing. Pence concluded by expressing his commitment to keeping the economy growing and making America safer and more prosperous.